OL,3,CCommons committee chairman says local
OL,4,Croads are 'riddled with potholes'
OL,6,FLocal road conditions in England have
OL,7,Fbeen branded "a national
OL,8,Fembarrassment" by the head of a House
OL,9,Fof Commons committee.
OL,11,FConservative MP Sir Geoffrey Clifton-
OL,12,FBrown, who chairs the Public Accounts
OL,13,FCommittee (PAC), warned that road
OL,14,Fusers are being put at risk from
OL,15,F"highways riddled with potholes".
OL,17,FA damning report by the committee
OL,18,Ffound the Department for Transport
OL,19,F(DfT) "has not taken responsibility"
OL,20,Ffor its role in how roads have
OL,21,Fdeteriorated.
