OL,3,CCommons committee chairman says local
OL,4,Croads are 'riddled with potholes'
OL,6,FThe AA said the total cost of fixing
OL,7,Fvehicles it attended in the UK that
OL,8,Fhad broken down because of poor road
OL,9,Fsurfaces in 2024 was #579 million.
OL,11,FThat is compared with #474 million
OL,12,Fduring the previous 12 months and is
OL,13,Fthe highest total on record.
OL,15,FCommon problems caused by potholes
OL,16,Finclude damaged shock absorbers,
OL,17,Fbroken suspension springs and
OL,18,Fdistorted wheels.
